-- Number of Turkish Millionaires Surpass 50,000, Vatan Reports
-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 2012-08-09T06:21:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/number-of-turkish-millionaires-surpass-50-000-vatan-reports.html
The number of millionaires in  Turkey 
increased by 7,931 to 50,844 over the past year, Vatan reported,
citing data from the Banking Regulation and Supervision Agency.  Turkish millionaires hold a total of 341 billion liras
($192 billion) in bank accounts, making up 47.5 percent of total
deposits in the country, the newspaper said.
